!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

imagine /ɪˈmædʒɪn/

(imagining,imagined,imagines) 

1. V-T If you imagine something, you think about it and your mind forms a picture or idea of it. 想像 

例： He could not imagine a more peaceful scene. 他想像不出比这更幽静的场景。 

2. V-T If you imagine that something is the case, you think that it is the case. 猜想 

例： I imagine you're referring to Jean-Paul Sartre. 我猜你指的是吉恩-保尔·萨特。 

3. V-T If you imagine something, you think that you have seen, heard, or experienced that thing, although actually you have not. 幻想 

例： Looking back on it now, I realized that I must have imagined the whole thing. 现在回想起来，我意识到这整个事情一定是我幻想出来的。

</div>

